trans-unit.source:
\n

Represents a non-generic collection of objects that can be individually accessed by index.

\n
trans-unit.target: $x$x$Xxxxxxxxxx x xxx$xxxxxxx xxxxxxxxxx xx xxxxxxx xxxx xxx xx xxxxxxxxxxxx xxxxxxxx xx xxxxx.$$x$$x

trans-unit.source:
\n

Gets or sets the element at the specified index.

\n
trans-unit.target: $x$x$Xxxx xx xxxx xxx xxxxxxx xx xxx xxxxxxxxx xxxxx.$$x$$x

trans-unit.source:
\n

The zero-based index of the element to get or set.
trans-unit.target: $x$x$Xxx xxxx$xxxxx xxxxx xx xxx xxxxxxx xx xxx xx xxx.

trans-unit.source:
\n

The position into which the new element was inserted, or -1 to indicate that the item was not inserted into the collection.

\n
trans-unit.target: $x$x$Xxx xxxxxxxx xxxx xxxxx xxx xxx xxxxxxx xxx xxxxxxxx$ xx $0 xx xxxxxxxx xxxx xxx xxxx xxx xxx xxxxxxxx xxxx xxx xxxxxxxxxx.$$x$$x

trans-unit.source:
\n

The index of value if found in the list; otherwise, -1.

\n
trans-unit.target: $x$x$Xxx xxxxx xx $xx$xxxxx$$xx$ xx xxxxx xx xxx xxxx$ xxxxxxxxx$ $0.$$x$$x

trans-unit.source:
\n

The zero-based index at which value should be inserted.
trans-unit.target: $x$x$Xxx xxxx$xxxxx xxxxx xx xxxxx $xx$xxxxx$$xx$ xxxxxx xx xxxxxxxx.

trans-unit.source:
\n

The zero-based index of the item to remove.
trans-unit.target: $x$x$Xxx xxxx$xxxxx xxxxx xx xxx xxxx xx xxxxxx.
